divs: Sighting DetailsI was outside with my family by the fire when i went into the house to let the dog outside to join us. It was getting late, anywhere between 11-12, when from the back porch I saw a steady, white star-like object pass slowly for about 30 seconds until it finally dimmed slowly until it went out. It was high up and only just as large as one of the stars. I don't know what I thought at first because the object was moving to slow to be a shooting star, and too fast to be a transiting planet. The object moved in a straight path, and seemed to be extremely high up.
